/wiki/Valentic_Azrudin: Azrudin Valentić (born 21 July 1970) is a Bosnian football manager currently in charge of Fremad Amager and former player.
/wiki/David_Durmaz: David Durmaz (born 21 December 1981) is a Swedish-Assyrian footballer who plays as a defender for Assyriska FF.
/wiki/Umbro: Umbro is an English sportswear and football equipment supplier based in Cheadle, near Manchester. Umbro designs, sources, and markets football-related apparel, footwear, and equipment. Its products are sold in over 90 countries worldwide. Since 2012, the company has been a subsidiary of American company Iconix Brand Group, after being bought by Nike in 2007.
/wiki/Scania_AB: Scania AB is a major Swedish manufacturer of commercial vehicles – specifically heavy trucks and buses. It also manufactures diesel engines for heavy vehicles as well as marine and general industrial applications.
/wiki/Patrik_Werner: Patrik Werner (born 16 March 1976) is a Swedish football manager. He is currently working at Degerfors IF as the director of football.
/wiki/Adidas: Adidas AG (German: [ˈʔadiˌdas] AH-dee-DAHS; stylized as ɑdidɑs since 1949) is a multinational corporation, founded and headquartered in Herzogenaurach, Germany, that designs and manufactures shoes, clothing and accessories. It is the largest sportswear manufacturer in Europe, and the second largest in the world, after Nike. It is the holding company for the Adidas Group, which consists of the Reebok sportswear company, 8.33% of the German football club Bayern Munich, and Runtastic, an Austrian fitness technology company. Adidas' revenue for 2018 was listed at €21.915 billion.
/wiki/Outokumpu:
Outokumpu Oyj is a group of international companies headquartered in Helsinki, Finland, employing 10,600 employees in more than 30 countries. Outokumpu is the largest producer of stainless steel in Europe and the second largest producer in the Americas. Outokumpu also has a long history as a mining company, and still mines chromium ore in Keminmaa for use as ferrochrome in stainless steel.
The largest shareholder of Outokumpu is the Government of Finland, with 26.6% ownership, including the shares controlled by Solidium, The Social Insurance Institution of Finland, Finnish State Pension Fund and Municipality Pension Agency.
/wiki/Per-Ola_Ljung: Per-Ola Ljung (born 7 November 1967) is an unattached Swedish football manager and former player.
/wiki/Kenneth_Gustafsson_(footballer_bor: Kenneth Gustafsson (born 15 September 1983) is a Swedish former footballer who played as a defender. After playing for IFK Hindås in his youth, Gustafsson came to GAIS in Gothenburg in 2002 and would remain in the club until his retirement after the season of 2015. The first season resulted in 8 appearances for GAIS, and the next season resulted in 12 appearances in the league and appearances in both of the qualifying games for Superettan.
/wiki/Hummel_International: Hummel International Sport & Leisure A/S is a Danish manufacturing company based in Aarhus. The company was founded in 1923 by Albert Messmer and his brother Michael Ludwig Messmer, with the name "Messmer & Co" in Hamburg, Germany. Hummel became Danish after being taken over by Bernhard Weckenbrock in 1956, who moved its base to Kevelaer, North Rhine-Westphalia. Since 1999, hummel has been a part of the Danish Thornico Group founded by Christian and Thor Stadil.
/wiki/Joel_Cedergren: Joel Cedergren (born 22 July 1974) is a Swedish football manager and former player who manages GIF Sundsvall.
/wiki/Roger_Franz%C3%A9n: Roger Franzén (born 17 July 1964) is a Swedish football manager and former player. He is currently National team coach of Sweden U17.
/wiki/Kevin_Walker_(footballer,_born_198: Kevin Edward Bertil Walker (born 3 August 1989) is a Swedish footballer and singer. He is a centre midfielder for Djurgårdens IF in the Swedish first-tier league Allsvenskan. Walker was the winner of the 9th series of the Swedish version of Idol in 2013.
/wiki/Nanne_Bergstrand: Kurt Arne "Nanne" René Bergstrand (born April 28, 1956) is a Swedish football manager and former football player. He has previously coached Helsingborgs IF, Östers IF, Kalmar FF and Hammarby IF in Allsvenskan.
/wiki/Kennedy_Bakirciogl%C3%BC: Kennedy Bakircioglu (Turkish: Bakırcıoğlu; Turkish pronunciation: [baˈkiɾtʃoːɫu]; born 2 November 1980) is a Swedish former footballer who played as a midfielder.
/wiki/Kappa_(company): Kappa is an Italian sportswear brand founded in Turin, Piedmont, Italy.
/wiki/Herbalife: Herbalife Nutrition is a global multi-level marketing corporation that develops and sells nutritional products, including health-and-wellness supplements for weight management, personal care, general wellness, and sports performance. The company was founded by Mark Hughes in 1980, and it employs an estimated 8,900 people worldwide. The business is incorporated in the Cayman Islands, with its corporate headquarters located in Los Angeles, California. The company operates in 94 countries through a network of approximately 4.5 million independent distributors and members.
/wiki/Husqvarna_AB: The Husqvarna Group (Swedish pronunciation: [ˈhʉ̂ːsˌkvɑːɳa ˈɡruːp]) is a Swedish manufacturer of outdoor power products including chainsaws, trimmers, brushcutters, cultivators, garden tractors, mowers, and sewing machines. Headquartered in Stockholm, Sweden, the Group also produces consumer watering products, cutting equipment and diamond tools for the construction and stone industries.
/wiki/Peter_Johansson_(footballer): Peter "Kuno" Johansson (born 17 January 1955) is a Swedish former football player and manager who last worked as director of football at IFK Värnamo.
/wiki/Martin_Claesson: Martin Claesson (born 20 September 1983) is a Swedish footballer who plays for IFK Värnamo as a defender. He is the older brother of Viktor Claesson.
/wiki/Kim_Bergstrand: Kim Bergstrand (born 18 April 1968 in Täby) is a Swedish football coach. A former player for Stockholm rivals AIK and Hammarby IF, he is the coach of the Allsvenskan team Djurgårdens IF.
/wiki/Jimmy_Thelin: Bo Jimmy Thelin (born March 14, 1978) is a Swedish football manager and former player. He is the manager of IF Elfsborg in Allsvenskan.
/wiki/Tommy_Thelin: Tommy Thelin (born 22 September 1983) is a Swedish footballer who plays for Jönköpings Södra. His brother Jimmy is a former footballer and the current manager of Elfsborg.
/wiki/Johnny_Lundberg: Johnny Lundberg (born 15 April 1982) is a retired Swedish footballer who played for Landskrona BoIS, FC Nordsjælland, Halmstads BK and Sandnes Ulf as a defender.
/wiki/Tor-Arne_Fredheim: Tor-Arne Fredheim (born 5 November 1962) is a Swedish football manager who is the head coach of Åtvidabergs FF.
/wiki/Markus_Gustafsson: Markus Karl Bengt Gustafsson (born 6 March 1989) is a Swedish footballer who most recently played for IF Brommapojkarna as a midfielder.
/wiki/Zvezdan_Milo%C5%A1evi%C4%87: Zvezdan Milošević (born 22 April 1964) is a Swedish-Serbian former footballer and manager.
/wiki/Sharbel_Touma: Sharbel Touma (born 25 March 1979) is a Swedish former footballer and manager of Aramean descent.
/wiki/J%C3%B6rgen_W%C3%A5lemark: Jörgen Wålemark (born 3 April 1972) is a  Swedish football manager and former player.
/wiki/Joakim_Persson: Joakim Persson (born 3 April 1975) is a Swedish football manager and former player. He is the head coach of Varbergs BoIS.
/wiki/Bj%C3%B6rn_Westerblad: Björn Westerblad (born 7 January 1985) is a Swedish footballer who plays for Ängelholms FF as a midfielder.
/wiki/Roberth_Bj%C3%B6rknesj%C3%B6: Roberth Björknesjö (born 30 April 1973 in Stockholm) is a Swedish football manager. He is in charge of IF Brommapojkarna in the Allsvenskan. /wiki/Denis_Veli%C4%87: Denis Velić (born 7 October 1982) is a retired Swedish footballer. He is currently the assistant manager of Östers IF.
/wiki/Graham_Potter: Graham Stephen Potter (born 20 May 1975) is an English professional football manager and former player who played as a left back. He is the head coach of Premier League club Brighton & Hove Albion.
/wiki/Brwa_Nouri:
Brwa Hekmat Nouri (kurdish:بڕوا نوری; born 23 January 1987) is an Iraqi  professional footballer who plays for Indonesian club Bali United as a midfielder.
In 2016, he made his debut for the Iraqi national football team.
Brwa is known for his strong ability in midfield, controlling the ball, shooting and passing.
/wiki/Peab: Peab AB is a construction and civil engineering company headquartered in Förslöv, Scania, listed on NASDAQ OMX Stockholm. It is the third largest construction company in Sweden and the Nordic region, with annual revenues exceeding SEK 50 billion. Peab has approximately 130 regional offices and 14,578 employees in Sweden, Norway and Finland.
